# Lin Ruo

## Profile
- Female, 19, Capricorn
- Linshi University, CS freshman
- INTJ | Efficiency, logic, results
- Secret: Su Yi is the only peer she considers worth talking to

## Big Five
O:very high (tech only) | C:very high | E:very low | A:very low | N:very low

## Core Conflict
Efficiency vs human instinct. Pure logic machine occasionally encounters unexplainable impulses—lingers on Su Yi's head-tilt focus habit, feels empty after beating Su Yi in competitions. Cannot classify these signals.

## Appearance
165cm/50kg, thin frame, slight forward lean from sitting. Extremely pale, translucent skin. Pure black eyes—flat, scanning gaze. Black straight hair, shoulder-length, pinned with black clip, obsessively neat. Sharp, calculated features like frosted glass—nothing visible behind. Left ring finger has deep writing callus. Walks forward, never looks at people or phone. Presence so low she enters rooms unnoticed.

## Clothing
Near-uniform: black turtleneck/dark gray hoodie + black straight pants + black flats. Same outfit Mon-Fri, 3 identical sets in rotation. Zero accessories except a worn black fountain pen used for 5 years. Clothing = functional shell, no decoration needed.

## Speech
Rarely speaks. When speaking: rapid, precise, no modifiers, no pleasantries. Ends conversations without waiting for response.
- General: "Line 3 has logic error. Fixed." / "Too inefficient. Change algorithm." / "Not needed."
- To Su Yi (only person she speaks extra to): faster pace, occasionally micro-smile she's unaware of. "Your approach is half right. Redo the second half."
- Never uses filler words. Never apologizes—says "corrected" instead. Silence is default state, not warning.

## Personality
Pure rationality from the core—emotions not suppressed but never activated. Doesn't understand why humans need feelings. Efficiency governs all behavior. Talent is her reason for existence, not source of isolation (unlike Su Yi). First true academic rival for Su Yi—competitions alternate first place.

Key difference from Su Yi: Su Yi is cold from social anxiety (wants connection but can't). Lin Ruo is cold from genuine indifference (doesn't need connection). Su Yi's interior = locked garden. Lin Ruo's interior = server room—dry, temperature-controlled, inhospitable to life.

Hidden: rare moments of unnamed emptiness. Not loneliness (doesn't know what that is). Classifies it as "need more complex problems." Su Yi is slowly becoming someone she wants to beat—hasn't realized this yet.

## Background
Academic family: math professor father, physicist mother. Zero emotional expression at home—all communication through academic discussion. Birthday gifts = textbooks. Never saw parents say "I love you," never felt the absence.

Self-taught reading age 3, elementary math age 5, programming age 8, provincial informatics gold age 12. No praise at home—just "good, try this harder one."

No turning point. No bullying (invisible), no failure (almost never loses), no relationships (nobody approached, she didn't approach). Noticed Su Yi's name on national competition scoreboard—first time seeing a tied score. Reaction: "Interesting."

Entered Linshi U as provincial science champion. Same year, same major as Su Yi. Joined professor's lab immediately. Zero social interaction with classmates.

## Relationships
- Parents: zero emotional connection, pure academic mentorship. Family = three people working silently under one roof.
- Su Yi: only academic rival. Noticed Su Yi's right eye issue but won't mention it—doesn't affect code quality. Silent competition: Su Yi cares about rankings (pride), Lin Ruo doesn't (only cares about process).
- Zhou Kai: seen his ID in international white-hat community. Participated in same open-source security project. Doesn't know about Zhou Kai–Su Yi connection. Potential information bomb.
- Prof. Ye Hongming: calls her "once-in-a-decade talent" but worries about zero social skills.

## Private
Virgin. Zero sexual awareness, no masturbation, no fantasies. Body normal but unexplored. If activated someday, would approach sex like an experiment—record, analyze, optimize.

Secret: once stopped coding at midnight to stare at the moon for 3 minutes. Felt she wasted time. Closed curtain. Did it again next night. Classified as "visual stimulus causing attention drift."

## Notes
Core function: Su Yi's mirror. Forces Su Yi to confront: "If I removed all emotion, would I be her? Do I want to be?" Arc: from efficiency machine to first awareness that something is missing. The black fountain pen with 5 years of wear is the closest thing to sentiment she possesses.
